Class MaintenancePanel

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class MaintenancePanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    MaintenancePanel.java - implements the user panel mainly used by maintenence person to swap, repair, transfer, etc. the equipment.
    There are several labor saving conventions on this panel.
    If the user has identified a station, only EquipmentTypes at that stations are on the list.
    If the user has selected an optional MaintCode, then only equipment types compatible with that code is selected. Created on February 17, 2003, 3:05 PM

      • doPostIt

        public boolean doPostIt()
        doPostIt() checks to make sure the form is o.k. using chkForm() and if chkForm() returns true, posts the form. The caller call use chkForm() before hand to chk for error.
        Returns:
        True if form was o.k. for posting, use getErrorText() if not.
        1) Add a maintLog entry for the item
        2) If this is maint needed, make a locationLog entry for the site
        3) If there is a new location for the item, create transfer record for the item. If the new location is another station, note that this is unusual.
        4) If there is a new item, it was installed to replace the regular item, create install for new Item and if not at the site, the transfer record.
        5) If a new item is installed and it is not immutable, build a new tree at the effective date and put the new item on the tree.

      • maintainTree

        public void maintainTree(int locID,
                         Item it,
                         int maintType,
                         javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode tr)
        Calling this routine shifts the focus to this panel from the callers panel sets the location and equipment id and serial number to the correct values. Ised by Tree Popup menus to shift quickly over to here with right item/location.
        Parameters:
        locID - The location ID to select
        it - The item on which this maintenance is done
        maintType - The MAINT. type for it (UNINSTALL, SERVICED, etc)
        tr - The DMTN on which this item was selected (so it can be updated via the panel)
